A high-angle macro photograph of the intermediate joint section of a carbon-fiber flight suit arm prototype. The multi-segment elbow accordion bellows, printed out of a flexible deep-purple thermoplastic polyurethane composite, are shown at their maximum contraction angle during a mechanical flex test. The inner crease roots catch crisp workshop cross-lighting, verifying absolute zero layer separation or structural pinholing along the seams. Handheld alignment rods and dry graphite micro-powder canisters lie scattered on an orange workshop matting bench, cleanroom prototype assembly focus, crisp details --ar 16:9
